sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as ODH Model Controller<br/>Webhook 443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as ODH Model Controller<br/>Reconcilers
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>5001/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant Activator as Knative Activator<br/>8012/TCP HTTP
    participant Pod as Inference Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant NGC as NVIDIA NGC API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 1: InferenceService Creation
    User->>K8sAPI: Submit InferenceService CR<br/>OIDC/Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated InferenceService
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-serving-kserve-io-v1beta1-inferenceservice<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation OK
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: InferenceService created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route, VirtualService, AuthConfig,<br/>ServiceMonitor, NetworkPolicy, PeerAuthentication<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>ModelReg: Register InferenceService metadata<br/>REST API (if MODELREGISTRY_STATE=enabled)
    KServe->>K8sAPI: Create Knative Service or Deployment<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 2: Inference Request (Serverless)
    User->>Route: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Route->>Gateway: Forward to Istio Gateway<br/>HTTP (plaintext)
    Gateway->>Authorino: Validate Auth Token<br/>gRPC mTLS (if AuthConfig enabled)
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK
    Gateway->>Activator: Route request<br/>HTTP (if pod scaled to zero)
    Activator->>Pod: Forward to predictor<br/>HTTP with mTLS (if PeerAuth enabled)
    Pod->>S3: Load model artifacts<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+ IAM/Access Key
    S3-->>Pod: Model data
    Pod-->>Activator: Inference result
    Activator-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 3: NIM Account Management
    User->>K8sAPI: Create NIM Account CR<br/>with NGC API key secret<br/>OIDC/Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-nim-opendatahub-io-v1-account<br/>mTLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation OK
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: Account created
    Controller->>NGC: Validate account, fetch model list<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3 NGC API Key
    NGC-->>Controller: Model catalog
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (model list),<br/>Secret (pull secret),<br/>Template (ServingRuntime)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    loop Every 24h (default)
        Controller->>NGC: Refresh model list<br/>HTTPS TLS1.3 NGC API Key
        NGC-->>Controller: Updated catalog
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ConfigMap<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    end

    Note over User,ModelReg: Flow 4: Metrics Collection
    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP<br/>Bearer Token (via ServiceMonitor)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Controller metrics
    Prometheus->>Pod: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP 8080/TCP mTLS<br/>Bearer Token (via ServiceMonitor/PodMonitor)
    Pod-->>Prometheus: Inference metrics
